name: Warung Day-U

review 1:
The food is traditional and the place looks very nice with the view of the rice terrace and the ocean. The food was very good, we had the Banana fitters (6 pieces in total) and the Nasi Campur but with dry fish.

review 2: A good place to spend the afternoon and enjoy its affordable menus. all food tastes good. I like the view of the vast rice field  and sea. review 3:
A nice local warung in the middle of beautiful rice paddies in Tabanan. We ordered mujair nyat-nyat, ikan goreng, ayam kecombrang and for dessert, banana fritters and everything was delicious.

Ibu Dayu herself served the food and spare her time to talk to us with her beautiful smile and a genuine Balinese hospitality.

After eating, we hang out at the warung just to enjoy the peaceful ambience that we couldn‚Äôt find anywhere else.
